The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Avik surgery today
                                                   Avik surgery today
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Things are not looking good for Bengal cricketer Avik Chowdhury who was cricitcally injured in car crash on Sunday.         
	Avik was taken to the Apollo Hospital from Ruby General Hospital on Thursday and a MRI revealed that the nerve from the brain to the spinal cord has been snapped. He has suffered transection of the spinal cord, Dr Shanti Ranjan Dasgupta, who was present during the MRI, said Thursday.         
	The 24-year-old cricketer will undergo a surgery on Friday morning. Dr Abrahar Ahmed will lead the team of surgeons. Sources said that the Dr Ahmed has been in constant touch with Dr Rajasekhar Reddy of Chennai via e-mail and it was the latters idea to go ahead with the surgery. It will be a seven-hour operation, hospital sources said.         
	Avik is developing bed sore since he cant move and the operation will be done so that there is at least some improvement. Even if he is out of ventilator, we cant say he is out of danger yet, hospital sources added.                                                                                                                       
